# Plotting
snowc_time_avg <- apply(ncvar_get(data, "snowc"), c(1, 2), mean, na.rm = TRUE)
mean_snowc <- melt(t(snowc_time_avg), 
                  c("Latitude", "Longitude"), value.name = "Percent")

mean_snowc$Latitude <- expand.grid(lat, lon)[ , 1]
mean_snowc$Longitude <- expand.grid(lat, lon)[ , 2]
plot=ggplot(mean_snowc, aes(Longitude, Latitude, fill = Percent)) +
  geom_tile()+scale_fill_gradient(low = "green", high = "red") +
  labs(title = "Mean snow cover (%) 2010-2020",
       x = "Longitude E (?)", y = "Latitude N (?)") +
  theme(aspect.ratio = 1)
plot + theme_bw()
